# Hot Sales Phase 2A — operational lane (drift stop)

**Authority:** [docs/hot-sales/PHASE-2A-OPS-GATE-REGISTER.md](docs/hot-sales/PHASE-2A-OPS-GATE-REGISTER.md) · [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) § Hot Sales Phase 2A

## Active phase

Phase 2A **implementation is closed** (tag `hot-sales-phase-2a` → `8e650ff`). Only **operational rollout** is in scope — primarily **Gate 4B** sales allowlist verification.

## Forbidden without explicit user approval

- Phase **2B, 2C, 2D** (finance, pickup, Excel, notifications, ERP)
- New Hot Sales permissions, roles, RBAC UI, schema migrations, or trade features
- Enabling `HOT_SALES_RBAC_ENABLED=true` (Gates 6–7)
- Repo normalization: `lib/`, `components/`, layout, declaration refactors mixed into Hot Sales work
- Guardian Auth / portal atmosphere changes framed as Hot Sales rollout

## Allowed (Ops lane)

- Gate 4B production data setup (`hot_sales_sales_member`, open events/products)
- Merge hotfix `4d203a7` (`fix/hot-sales-next-intl-trade-shell`) to `main`
- Production-blocking emergency fixes on the frozen boundary
- Test-lane commits **after** Gate 4B closes (separate from deploy)

## Test identity (do not conflate)

- `SHARED_ADMIN_EMAIL` — admin matrix, not sales allowlist tests
- `PREVIEW_CLIENT_EMAIL` — S16 declaration preview client; **not** auto-seeded into `hot_sales_sales_member`
- Redirect to `/client` after `/trade` for non-allowlisted users is **expected**, not RBAC regression

## Before coding

Read the gate register. If the task is not Gate 4B, hotfix merge, or production-blocking fix — **stop and ask** whether scope changed.
